A MAN has been arrested in connection with an alleged robbery at a Glasgow hairdressers. Man arrested over raid at hair salon A MAN has been arrested in connection with an alleged robbery at a Glasgow hairdressers.Officers were called to the Shettleston area of the city at around 10.30am yesterday after the alarm was raised.Police rushed to the scene, in Wellshot Road, as the investigation got underway.A 44-year-old man was arrested shortly after the alleged incident.He is expected to appear at Glasgow Sheriff Court on Monday.Eyewitnesses said there was a large police presence in Shettleston following the incident.Police Scotland's helicopter was also deployed.A police spokeswoman said: &quot;A 44-year-old man was arrested in connection with an alleged robbery.&quot; 